HOW TO
======

Prepare for commit

prepare -m LATEST -r
Use -r for RCS style merge


To make view from an existing branch:

mkview -i <branch> -v <vob_tag> -s <storage> { -t <optional_tag_name> }



To make label:

Note: label can only be applied to the main or integration branch.
      You cannot make label on a task branch.

- mklabel -l LABEL_NAME(ALL CAPITAL)
          [-co "comment"]



To create integration branch:

- make a view from the parent branch, if needed
- set view to this view
- create a base label on the parent branch, if needed
- mkbrtype -v <vob>
           -b <new_branch_name>
           -base_label <label>
           -s FEA_INT


To print out history of a file in current directory make in a branch:
  ct lsh -branch <branch_name> <filename>
Omit filename if for all files in current directory


To move a view to another machine:
  cc_mv_view -t <viewname> -p <new_storage> -m <new_hostname> -v <vob_name>
  After verifying the view on the same machine, need to manually remove
  the old storage at <old_storage>/OLD.<viewname>
  If you get error message (Access denied),
  try "/usres/groeck/bin/cc_mv_view.local" instead.


To sync an integration branch with its parent:
  - assumptions:
    vob: /vob/rmx
    child branch: child_integ
    parent branch: parent_integ
  - make sure CLEARCASW_AVOBS environment include the vob.


To remove identical files during a prepare:
  cc_rm_identical
In case this does not work, make sure those files are really identical and
edit the ViewAudit file to remove those entries.  The ViewAudit file can be
found under /vws/noa/<view name>/cisco/audit/.  It contains the change set
of the view.


To pull a throttle branch:
  mkbrtype -base_label <label>
           -b <throttle branch name>
           -v <vob>
           -s THROTTLE
           -p <parent branch name>


To check into a throttle branch:
  First create a DDTS entry if you do not already one
  Add the DDTS id to the following two files:
    /vbs/bfb/rmx/cisco/audit/<throttle branch name>/RestrictedToBugs-<throttle branch name>
    /vbs/bfb/rmx/cisco/xaudit/<throttle branch name>/RestrictedToBugs-<throttle branch name>
    (You may need to create the directory with your throttle branch name under
     audit and xaudit, if they are not already there!)
  Then check in as normal.


To find all labels in the RMX vob, visit the directory
  /auto/vbsbfb/rmx/cisco/audit/labels


The audit directory for VNBU IOS code is:
  /auto/scmlog/ios/<branch_name>
The audit directory for VNBU QNX code is:
  /auto/scmlog/qnx/<branch_name>

The list of committed patches of a branch can be found in CommitPatches under
the audit directory.  Ex: /auto/scmlog/qnx/<branch>/CommitPatches

Clearcase help page:
  wwwin-swtools.cisco.com/swtools/clearcase/howto


Graphically diff two files:
  ct diff -g file1 file2


To find out what files have been checked out in a view:
  ct lsp -co


To sync the vob:
  fix_audit
  cc_update -m LATEST


To create a new component:
cc_create_comp -pseudo -component rfgw/sim/video -vob /vob/ios.comp


To do static analysis (SA):
prep-commit <DDTS>


